@node Azioni "Menu Actions"

 @{b}Actions menu items@{ub}

 @{"Open full tree" link espandi_tutto}
 @{"Close tree    " link chiudi_tutto}

@endnode

@node espandi_tutto "'Open full tree' menu item"

 Selecting this item will expand all the directories in the tree,
 including their subdirectories. In other words, the whole tree will
 be shown. This operation could take some time; it depends on the
 number of files on your filesystem.

@endnode

@node chiudi_tutto "'Close tree' menu item"

 All the directories in the tree will be collapsed, returning the tree
 to its initial state.

@endnode

@node Progetto "Project menu"

 @{b}Project menu items@{ub}

 @{"Load Tree        " link Carica_albero}
 @{"Save Tree        " link Salva_albero}
 @{"Save Default Tree" link default}
 @{"New Tree         " link Genera_albero}
 @{"Info             " link Info}
 @{"Quit             " link Quit}

@endnode

@node default "'Save Default Tree' menu item"

 Selecting this item, you will save the current tree as "DEFAULT.tree".
 This file is automatically loaded by AmyTree during startup.

@endnode

@node Carica_albero "'Load Tree' menu item"

 This item lets you load a previously saved tree via a filerequester.
 Only files with extension ".tree" are displayed.

@endnode

@node Salva_albero "'Save tree' menu item"

 This item lets you save the current tree on disk. This is
 particularly useful with rarely updated directories or @{" CDs " link CD}.
 You can generate the whole tree of a CD (or, better, only a part of
 the tree) and then save it; the next time you want to browse that CD,
 you can just insert it and load the corresponding file from disk.
 The extension ".tree" will be automatically added to the filename you
 choose if missing.
 If you save a tree with the name "default.tree" in AmyTree's
 directory, it will be automatically loaded at every startup.

@endnode

@node Genera_albero "'New Tree' menu item"

 Select this item and you will get a directory requester asking you
 for the root of the filesystem tree to generate.

@endnode

@node Info "'Info' menu item"

 This item will show my address ;-).

@endnode

@node Quit "'Quit' menu item"

 I can't find a good reason to select this item. :-)

@endnode

@node Preferenze "Prefs menu"

 @{b}Prefs menu items@{ub}

 @{"Conf. Button    " link configurazione}
 @{"NoScroller      " link noscroller}
 @{"Fonts           " link fonts}
 @{"Icon            " link icon}

@endnode

@node icon

  @{b}Icon@{ub}

  This item lets you iconize AmyTree. Once iconized, a double click
  on its icon will un-iconize it, returning to the previous state.
  If you drop a drawer on AmyTree's icon, the program will re-open its
  window using the drawer you dropped as new root of the tree.

@endnode

@node fonts

 @{b}Fonts@{ub}

 Don't use this feature in the current release; it is still not fully
 implemented.

@endnode

@node noscroller

 @{b}NoScroller@{ub}

 When this option is on, the real-time scrolling of the tree is not
 active.

@endnode

@node configurazione "Configuration"

@{b}Configuring the gadgets@{ub}

This item will show a panel in which you will find the various gadgets
to which you can associate a program to run. In the first string
gadget you should type the path of the program you want to execute
(you can also use the small button on the right of the string gadget).
In the string gadget on the right you can type any option needed by
the program you selected on the left one.

@endnode

@node Descrizione_dei_gadget "Gadgets description"

@{b}Gadgets@{ub}

@{"   Open   " link apri}   @{"  Close   " link chiudi}
@{"OpenBranch" link branch}   @{"  Search  " link cerca}

@{"ViewDT " link viewdt}   @{"Info   " link infofile}
@{"Show   " link show}   @{"Play   " link play}
@{"User gadget" link usr}

@{"ListFiles" link list}

@{"I" link iconify}

@endnode

@node iconify

 This gadget iconifies AmyTree.

@endnode

@node branch "OpenBranch button"

@{b}OpenBranch@{ub}

 This gadget will expand the whole branch of the selected node.

@endnode


@node apri "Open button"

 @{b}Open@{ub}

 This gadget will expand the currently selected directory in the tree.
 The gadget is ghosted when the selected node is not a directory, or
 when it is a directory but cannot be expanded (a directory can be
 expanded when the small box before its name contains a "+" symbol).

 You can obtain the same effect by double-clicking the node you wish
 to expand.

@endnode

@node chiudi "Close button"

 @{b}Close@{ub}

 This is the opposite of @{"Open" link apri}; this gadget collapse the
 currently selected directory. The gadget is ghosted when the selected
 node is not an expanded directory (a directory can be collapsed when
 the small box before its name contains a "-" symbol).

 You can obtain the same effect by double-clicking the node you wish
 to collapse.

@endnode

@node viewdt "ViewDT button"

 @{b}ViewDT@{ub}

 This gadget will hand down the file selected in the listview above it
 to the datatypes you have installed in your system; if the file is not
 recognized by any of them, an error message will be displayed.
 The gadget is ghosted when no file is selected.

 See @{"Shortcomings" link Limitazioni}.

@endnode

@node infofile "Info button"

 @{b}Info@{ub}

 This gadget will show several informations on the selected file
 (name, size, date, file type etc.). The gadget is ghosted when no
 file is selected.

@endnode

@node cerca "Search button"

 @{b}Search@{ub}

 This gadget will open a requester asking you to type a string
 (directory name) to search in the tree. You can specify here partial
 names, and obviously the search is @{b}not@{ub} case-sensitive
 (actually, all the grunt work is performed by Strnicmp() from
 the utility.library :-)
 If the search was successfull, the node found will be put into view
 and will become the currently selected node; in any case, a requester
 will ask you if you want to continue the search or not.
 If no node matched the string you are searching for, AmyTree will
 call the DisplayBeep() function (and it will either flash the screen,
 ring a bell or both, according to your system preferences).

 This gadget is never ghosted.

@endnode

@node show "Show button"

 @{b}Show@{ub}

 This gadget will start a picture viewer @{"of your choice" link
 visualizzatore}, giving the name of the currently selected file as
 command-line argument.

 @{b}N.B.@{ub}
 Actually, AmyTree does not check the type of the file when you click
 "Show", so you can associate every kind of program to this gadget.
 However, unlike the user gadgets, the label cannot be changed.

@endnode

@node play "Play button"

 @{b}Play@{ub}

 This gadget will start a player of your choice, passing the name of
 the currently selected file as command-line argument. I use
 HippoPlayer, but any other player will do.

 This gadget is ghosted when the currently selected node is not a
 file.

 @{b}N.B.@{ub}
 Actually, AmyTree does not check the type of the file when you click
 "Play", so you can associate every kind of program to this gadget.
 However, unlike the user gadgets, the label cannot be changed.

@endnode

@node usr "User gadgets"

 @{b}User gadgets@{ub}

 You can assign to these gadgets a label and a program to run when they
 are clicked on. These programs will be given the name of the currently
 selected node as command-line argument.

@endnode

@node list "List Files button"

 @{b}List files@{ub}

 This gadget will toggle between active and ghosted file listview.
 You can improve tree navigation speed by activating the listview only
 when you actually need it.

@endnode

@node Limitazioni "Shortcomings and bugs"

 The current release of the program is certainly not perfect.

 Shortcomings:

 - The datatype viewer window cannot be resized.

 - The GUI is optimized for a 640x256 screen.


 @{b}BUGS:(@{ub}

 - there is some problem in viewing AmigaGuide files via datatypes.
   You can avoid these problem by assigning Multiview or a similar
   program to one of the user gadget.

 - other bugs: waiting for your mails!

@endnode

@node Descrizione_del_programma "Description of the program"

 @{b}What is AmyTree@{ub}

 AmyTree, in its current version, is a filesystem browser.
 AmyTree graphically represents a filesystem as a tree of directories.

 See @{"Usage" link Utilizzo_del_programma}

@endnode

